  "text": "Dietary patterns of mothers and fathers during pregnancy (baseline) and children at the age of five years were defined using principal components analysis (PCA), an a posteriori data reduction technique which identifies underlying patterns in food intake. The original list of 149 food items from the adult FFQ was reduced to 40 food items by grouping food items together which were similar in composition or nutrient value (for instance Crackers were included with \"white bread\"). The food groups for the analysis were based on those published by the Southampton Women's Study (SWS) which also examines diet in pregnancy, in a sample similar to the Lifeways population, using a FFQ instrument [CITATION_1] .",
